review_blob: the aroma reminds me of fresh baked bread straight from the oven. slight bitterness on the front that fades to sweet yeasty finish with a hint of banana. i really enjoyed this beer. nothing too overwhelming
on tap at rehoboth brewpub. a very nice sessionable pilsner. lots of hops flavor with a sweet aroma. not your typical pilsner but isnt that what you expect from dogfish.
great hoppy aroma. strong bitterness on initial taste. after the bitterness gets on your palate you can begin to taste the other complex flavors. love the artwork on the bottle.
beer_name: Three Floyds Fantabulous Resplendence (X Anniversary Ale)

review_blob: i love champagne so i enjoy the bubbly carbonation of this beer. a fun drink for celebratory purposes. it would be great for a toast at a beer lovers wedding. aroma is sweet with a very oaky flavor.
apicot is completely overdone in this beer. too sweet, like a childs fruit juice. the apricot/peachy flavor needs to better balanced.
i was not a big fan of this beer. a growler from the brewery. has a sweet some what perfume aroma. tasted very floral to me. dont think i will have it again.
smells like a fresh blueberry muffin.  has a light carbonation and taste of blueberries. it has definite black pepper taste in the finish. very strange beer. cant imagine drinking more than one.

very cloudy golden amber with a full frothy white head. delicious aroma of yeast and wheat.  i found the taste a disappointment from the aroma. sweet and crisp on the front. the tastes faded into a slightly watered down coffee flavor. i had hoped for more.
pours a cloudy  golden color. a nice citrus hoppy aroma.  sweet on front with a bitter finish.  a nice crisp refreshing brew.
i would like to give a lower score but it is not possible. i would not waste the lime to put in it. smells and tastes very skunky.

on tap at brewery and from growler. ive had this beer a few times and it is an easy fruit beer to drink. not overly tart and fruity like others i have had. light burgundy color.  taste of raspberries with a light tartiness in the finish.
draught at the brewery. Golden amber color. citrus aroma. taste of citrus and some floral undertones with a bitter finish.
pours thick black with a caramel head. sweet caramel and smoky aroma. very strong smoky flavor. very creamy and thick. a good imperial stout but definitely not my favorite.
beer_name: The Duck-Rabbit Rabid Duck Russian Imperial Stout

review_blob: poured cloudy golden amber. nice hoppy aroma. love the lemony hop taste. i could sit down and drink a lot of these. fantastic APA.
great well balanced version of an american wheat. has a nice hoppy aroma. you can definitely taste the hops in this beer. delicious lemony citrus finish. you can hardly recognize the wheat.
